"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-07-17-reps-gift-n100-million-to-nigerian-olympic-team\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  The House of Representatives has donated N100 million to the Nigerian Olympic team for the Paris Olympics.  The Deputy Speaker, Ben Kalu, announced this on Wednesday when the House hosted the Minister of Sport, John Enoh, and the team during plenary.  The Deputy Speaker announced that the money would be taken from the salaries of the members.  \\\"The money is coming from our salaries,\\\" Mr Kalu said.  Additionally, the Chairman of the House Committee on Army, Aminu Balele (APC, Katsina), donated N3 million to the team. The money was presented during plenary.  Declare State of Emergency on 10 Delta roads - Group tells Police Commissioner  Lagos govt denies re-introducing monthly environmental sanitation  Reps condemn killing of security personnel in Kebbi, order immediate clearance operation  Reps ask FG to name sponsors of terrorism, banditry  Insecurity: Armed Forces alone cannot solve Nigeria's challenges - Musa  Terrorists' financiers in Nigeria can not be tried in public - Reps member, Benson  Kebbi schoolgirls: Reps condemn alleged FG negotiation with bandits  Kebbi abduction: Reps urge Gov Idris to rename Maga school after slain vice principal  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"